          "gap": 32,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "D5tc1",
              "name": "articleRail",
              "width": 120,
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 10,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "cimsb",
                  "name": "articleMark",
                  "fill": "#6B7280",
                  "content": "02 / NOTE",
                  "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                  "fontSize": 13,
                  "fontWeight": "500",
                  "letterSpacing": 0.048
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "BV1AK",
                  "name": "articleLine",
                  "fill": "#4B5563",
                  "width": 2,
                  "height": 1860
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "Ixu9F",
              "name": "main",
              "width": 720,
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 34,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "PnYIN",
                  "name": "meta",
                  "fill": "$color-text-secondary",
                  "content": "02 / WRITING · 17 APR 2026 · AI SYSTEMS",
                  "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                  "fontSize": 13,
                  "fontWeight": "500",
                  "letterSpacing": 0.048
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "B6OeT",
                  "name": "articleNote",
                  "fill": "$color-text-secondary",
                  "content": "NOTE / AI SYSTEMS",
                  "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                  "fontSize": 13,
                  "fontWeight": "500",
                  "letterSpacing": 0.048
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "SayNq",
                  "name": "title",
                  "fill": "#111111",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": 720,
                  "content": "Designing AI systems\npeople can\nactually trust",
                  "lineHeight": 1.1,
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 64,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.01
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "2UuNb",
                  "name": "articleAnn",
                  "fill": "$color-text-secondary",
                  "content": "// trust is designed in the surrounding workflow",
                  "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                  "fontSize": 13,
                  "fontWeight": "500",
                  "letterSpacing": 0.048
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "jcv8I",
                  "name": "dek",
                  "fill": "#111827",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": 640,
                  "content": "Reliability in AI products is not a model benchmark problem alone. It is a product systems problem involving confidence, legibility, intervention design, and operational fallback.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 16
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "8uBCD",
                  "name": "body",
                  "width": 640,
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 22,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "VhSch",
                      "name": "p1",
                      "fill": "#111827",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 640,
                      "content": "The common failure mode in AI product design is assuming that better output quality will naturally produce user trust. In practice, trust is built when the system makes its behavior interpretable under pressure. People need to know what the system is doing, how certain it is, and what happens when it is wrong.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.6,
                      "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                      "fontSize": 18
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "hjIj9",
                      "name": "c7",
                      "width": 612,
                      "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": 0,
                        "fill": "#FFFFFF"
                      },
                      "gap": 10,
                      "padding": [
                        20,
                        16,
                        10,
                        16
                      ],
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "rectangle",
                          "id": "y9gNr",
                          "fill": "#9CA3AF",
                          "width": 2,
                          "height": "fill_container"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "iT5yQ",
                          "fill": "#111111",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": 548,
                          "content": "A trustworthy AI system does not hide uncertainty. It gives uncertainty a usable interface.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.7,
                          "fontFamily": "Geist",
                          "fontSize": 20,
                          "fontWeight": "600"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "SIDCi",
                      "name": "p2",
                      "fill": "#111827",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 640,
                      "content": "That means product leaders have to design more than prompts and outputs. They have to design review paths, confidence thresholds, visible failure states, and escalation logic. Once automation is attached to operational workflows, the surrounding control system matters as much as the model itself.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.6,
                      "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                      "fontSize": 18
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "VgKAD",
                      "name": "bodyAnn",
                      "fill": "#6B7280",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 584,
                      "content": "// the control layer is part of the product",
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "500",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.06
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "SrIy4",
                      "name": "c9",
                      "width": 612,
                      "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": 0,
                        "fill": "#FFFFFF"
                      },
                      "gap": 10,
                      "padding": [
                        20,
                        16,
                        10,
                        16
                      ],
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "rectangle",
                          "id": "oHpUP",
                          "fill": "#9CA3AF",
                          "width": 2,
                          "height": "fill_container"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "NdLA9",
                          "fill": "#111827",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": 548,
                          "content": "The product decision is not whether automation is possible. It is whether the system still behaves well when reality gets noisy.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.78,
                          "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                          "fontSize": 18,
                          "fontWeight": "normal",
                          "fontStyle": "italic"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "SlxON",
                      "name": "p3",
                      "fill": "#111827",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 640,
                      "content": "This is where systems thinking becomes practical. Good teams map where confidence should be high, where review is mandatory, and where override paths need to remain human-first. They avoid binary thinking about 'manual' versus 'automated' work and instead design a gradient of assistance tied to risk.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.6,
                      "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                      "fontSize": 18
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "LIKri",
                      "name": "c8",
                      "width": 612,
                      "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": 0,
                        "fill": "#FFFFFF"
                      },
                      "gap": 10,
                      "padding": [
                        20,
                        16,
                        10,
                        16
                      ],
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "rectangle",
                          "id": "g0yjG",
                          "fill": "#9CA3AF",
                          "width": 2,
                          "height": "fill_container"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "6CxJQ",
                          "fill": "#111111",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": 548,
                          "content": "If the workflow breaks trust at the moment of exception, scale only amplifies the damage.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.7,
                          "fontFamily": "Geist",
                          "fontSize": 20,
                          "fontWeight": "500"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "aXRZl",
                      "name": "p4",
                      "fill": "#111827",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 640,
                      "content": "The strategic implication is simple: leaders should treat trust as part of product architecture. It needs instrumentation, design ownership, and explicit tradeoff decisions. Otherwise, the system may appear efficient while quietly becoming brittle.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.6,
                      "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                      "fontSize": 18
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "1wGj4",
                  "name": "footer",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "padding": [
                    22,
                    0,
                    0,
                    0
                  ],
                  "justifyContent": "space_between",
                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "SPMir",
                      "name": "footName",
                      "fill": "$color-text-primary",
                      "content": "Prateek Khare",
                      "fontFamily": "Geist",
                      "fontSize": 18,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "xRxdQ",
                      "name": "footLinks",
                      "fill": "$color-accent",
                      "content": "Back to blog -> LinkedIn -> Email",
                      "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "600",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.048
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
